  "prompt": "What is the valid reason for India only getting a few medals in the Olympics?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why India has historically underperformed in the Olympics:\n\n1. Limited Sports Infrastructure\n- Lack of world-class training facilities\n- Inadequate sports infrastructure in most states\n- Limited investment in sports development\n\n2. Financial Constraints\n- Limited government funding for sports\n- Low financial support for athletes\n- Lack of corporate sponsorships\n\n3. Cultural Factors\n- Less emphasis on sports as a career option\n- Priority given to academic education\n- Limited sports culture compared to other countries\n\n4. Talent Identification and Development\n- Poor talent scouting system\n- Insufficient coaching and training programs\n- Limited opportunities for young athletes\n\n5. Population Focus\n- Concentrated on cricket rather than Olympic sports\n- Less exposure to international sports competitions\n\n6. Systemic Issues\n- Bureaucratic sports administration\n- Corruption in sports organizations\n- Slow decision-making processes\n\n7. Resource Allocation\n- Limited resources for multiple sports\n- Concentration on select sports like cricket\n\n8. Economic Challenges\n- Limited resources for comprehensive sports development\n- Poverty and economic constraints limiting sports participation\n\nDespite these challenges, India has been improving its Olympic performance in recent years, with more medals and better athlete preparation.",
